# BBG Primary Skill Entrypoints

BBG primary skill entrypoints are repository-local and must not be installed globally.

Always load `AGENTS.md` and `RULES.md` before using a BBG entrypoint so the local project governance and coding constraints remain authoritative.

When the user intent matches one of these first-level workflows, read the referenced canonical skill before acting:

- Analyze: `.bbg/harness/skills/analyze/SKILL.md`
- Add Repo: `.bbg/harness/skills/add-repo/SKILL.md`
- Start: `.bbg/harness/skills/start/SKILL.md`
- Resume: `.bbg/harness/skills/resume/SKILL.md`
- Deliver: `.bbg/harness/skills/deliver/SKILL.md`

Do not expose internal BBG skills as user choices. Internal skills such as `workflow`, `model-route`, `task-start`, `analyze-repo`, `cross-audit`, and `hermes` are invoked only through the primary entrypoints above.

Trigger examples:

- `bbg analyze`, `analyze skill`, `项目分析`, `业务分析`, `技术架构分析` -> Analyze
- `add repo`, `添加仓库`, `注册子项目` -> Add Repo
- `start task`, `开始需求`, `开始开发` -> Start
- `resume`, `继续任务`, `恢复上下文` -> Resume
- `deliver`, `交付报告`, `客户报告` -> Deliver
